<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 02 at 3:57AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Pushmataha, Latimer,
southwestern Le Flore and southeastern Pittsburg Counties through 430
AM CDT...
At 357 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 5 miles southwest of Robbers Cave State Park to
10 miles southeast of Nashoba. Movement was northeast at 4o mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Wilburton...                      Clayton...
Hartshorne...                     Talihina...
Red Oak...                        Albion...
Talimena State Park...            Higgins...
Snow...                           Tuskahoma...
Stanley...                        Kiamichi...
Whitesboro...                     Clayton Lake State Park...
Damon...                          Bengal...
Yanush...                         Robbers Cave State Park...
Nashoba...                        Oleta...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
